olocaust, and the figure of Adolf Hitler himself. By exploring the origins of these works and assessing the controversies they have sparked in the United States and Europe, Hi Hitler! offers a fascinating and timely analysis of the shifting status of the Nazi past in western memory"--cProvided by publisher.  a16 4310aHitler, Adolf,d1889-1945. 0aWorld War, 1939-1945zGermany. 0aNational socialismxHistory. 0aHolocaust, Jewish (1939-1945)xHistory and criticism. 0aImaginary historiesxHistory and criticism. 0aAlternative histories (Fiction)xHistory and criticism. 0aCollective memory.423Cover imageuhttp://assets.cambridge.org/97811070/73999/cover/9781107073999.jpg  aD 757 R685 2015c1hUAAU-Bi0162035229853  aD 757 R685 2015wLCc1i0162035229853d9/25/2015e9/1/2015lON_SHELFmUAAUGn8p$150.00rYsYtBOOKu2/4/2015  aD 757 R685 2015wLCc1i0162035290590d11/29/2015e11/8/2015lON_SHELFmUAHSSn2p$150.00rYsYtBOOKu5/22/2015zCOUTTS_ADD01bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/38190770